{
  "texts": [
    "Rather than maximizing the marginal likelihood directly, we learn a parameterized reward r ϕ (a, q) over QA pairs such that optimizing a policy π θ (a | q) with respect to r ϕ yields a \"near-optimal\" policy that approximately maximizes the ML objective.",
    "We formalize \"near-optimality\" via the KL-regularized reward-maximization objective, and under this objective, it can be shown (Peng et al., 2019) that the optimal policy has the following closedform solution:",
    "where Z θ ⋆ (ϕ) (q) is the partition function, π ref is a fixed reference policy, and β > 0 controls the strength of the KL-regularization.",
    "See Appendix A.1 for the proof.",
    "Reward Gradient."
  ]
}